  focus:"文法焦點：對等連接詞 + 從屬連接詞",
  reading:{title:"The Demon in the Pot",
    en:"Gyokko, the Upper Rank Five, attacked the Swordsmith Village, a hidden place where the slayers' special blades were made. Gyokko was strange and cruel, but he was also very powerful. He could hide inside a pot or travel through water, so he was hard to catch. The village was usually quiet, so the sudden attack shocked everyone. Muichiro Tokito, the young Mist Hashira, did not fear him, although Gyokko was an Upper Moon. Because the swordsmiths were in great danger, Muichiro rushed to protect them. When the battle began, the demon laughed, but the young Hashira fought with cold focus. Even though Muichiro was tired, he never stopped. In the end, the village survived because the slayers refused to give up, and the swordsmiths could keep making their blades.",
    zh:"上弦之伍玉壺攻擊了刀匠之里——一個隱密之處，隊士的特殊刀就在那裡打造。玉壺古怪又殘忍，卻也非常強大。他能躲進壺中、穿水而行，因此難以捕捉。村子平時寧靜，這突如其來的攻擊嚇壞了所有人。年輕的霞柱時透無一郎並不怕他，儘管玉壺是上弦之鬼。因為刀匠們身陷危險，無一郎趕去保護他們。戰鬥開始時，那隻鬼大笑，但年輕的柱以冷靜的專注應戰。即使疲憊，無一郎也從未停下。最後村子得以倖存，因為隊士拒絕放棄，刀匠們也能繼續打造刀刃。"},
